ritten in the same place and time but in other languages, including Latin, Hebrew, Norse, Catalan, and Italian. Genres include love songs, satires, invectives, pastourelles, debates, laments, and religious songs. A comprehensive introduction places the troubadours in their historical context and traces the development of their art; headnotes introduce each poet, and the book ends witha bibliography and suggestions for further reading. WILLIAM D. PADEN is a Professor of French and Italian at Northwestern University, and was recently named a Chevalier dans l'Ordre des Palmes Académiques. FRANCES FREEMAN PADEN is a Distinguished Senior Lecturer in The Writing Program and Gender Studies, also at Northwestern University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aProvençal poetryvTranslations into English. 0aProvençal poetryvTranslations into English. 0aTroubadour songsvTranslations into English. 4aMedieval Literature. 4aMusic. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aDebates.  aInvectives.  aLaments.  aLove Songs.  aMedieval Poetry.  aOccitan Language.  aPastourelles.  aReligious Songs.  aSatires.  aSouth of France.  aTroubadour Poems.1 aPaden, Frances Freeman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaden, William D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846156014?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846156014423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846156014/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles